    • bestGuess

      @Deprecated(since="0.1.0") @API(status=DEPRECATED, since="0.0.5") public static final ClassNameImpl bestGuess(CharSequence className)
      Deprecated.
      Because of the limitations described above, this method is seen as inherently unsafe, and therefore it was decided to deprecate it.
      Returns a new ClassName instance for the given fully-qualified class name string. This method assumes that the input is ASCII and follows typical Java style (lowercase package names, UpperCamelCase class names) and may produce incorrect results or throw IllegalArgumentException otherwise. For that reason, get(Class), get(CharSequence,CharSequence,CharSequence...), and get(TypeElement) should be preferred as they can correctly create ClassName instances without such restrictions.
      Parameters:
      className - The fully qualified class name.
      Returns:
      The new class name instance.
